# Exam Result Email Automation — Context Brief

> Optimized for Claude Code sessions. Read this first when resuming work.

## What This Is

A Windows desktop app (PySide6) for university Registrar Office staff to generate and send personalized exam result emails from an Excel spreadsheet via Microsoft Outlook or SMTP.

## Current State

- **Version:** 0.5.0
- **Tests:** 55 passing (`python3 -m pytest -q`)
- **Platform:** Windows target, macOS development
- **Branch:** main — working tree clean

## Quick Commands

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate       # Python 3.12 venv
python3 -m pytest -q            # 55 tests in ~0.6s
python3 app.py                  # Launch GUI
```

## Architecture

```
GUI (PySide6) → Services → Business Logic → Models
```

### Source Tree

```
src/exam_email_automation/
├── config/         config_loader.py     — YAML → frozen Config dataclass
├── email/          email_builder.py     — composes EmailMessage, override_subject
│                   email_sender.py     — Outlook COM (pywin32), shared mailbox
│                   smtp_sender.py      — SMTP via smtplib
│                   delivery_mode.py    — PREVIEW_ONLY / CREATE_DRAFTS / SEND_IMMEDIATELY
├── excel/          excel_reader.py     — pandas .xlsx parser, student grouping, extra_fields
├── gui/            main_window.py      — QMainWindow, full wizard flow, template upload
│                   validation_dialog.py, confirmation_dialog.py,
│                   delivery_method_dialog.py, delivery_mode_dialog.py,
│                   results_dialog.py, dialogs.py, widgets.py
├── logging/        logger.py           — app logger + AuditLogger (timestamped .xlsx)
├── models/         student.py          — Student dataclass (+ extra_fields dict)
│                   module_result.py    — ModuleResult frozen dataclass
├── services/       preview_service.py  — HTML preview generation
│                   send_service.py     — mode/provider dispatch, batch send
├── templates/      template_engine.py  — Jinja2 ChoiceLoader (DictLoader + FileSystemLoader)
│                   docx_parser.py      — parse .docx, extract {{variables}}, → HTML
│                   template_metadata.py— TemplateMeta, companion YAML
│                   template1-3.html    — bundled HTML fallback templates
└── validation/     validator.py        — dynamic column validation, MismatchReport
```

### Key Design Decisions

- **Template-first workflow (Sprint 5):** Staff upload Word .docx with `{{variables}}` → tool extracts vars → validates Excel columns against vars → renders HTML
- **Outlook primary, SMTP fallback:** SendService dispatches based on config/provider selection
- **Draft-by-default:** `create_drafts` is the default delivery mode to prevent accidental mass sends
- **Layered architecture:** Business logic has zero GUI imports — all backend is testable without a display
- **Per-student failure isolation:** One failed email doesn't stop the batch
- **extra_fields on Student:** Any Excel column beyond the 12 known ones lands in `extra_fields` (keys normalized: lowercase, spaces→underscores)

## Current Workflow

```
Upload .docx Template (optional) → Browse Excel → Validate → Preview →
Choose Delivery Method (Outlook/SMTP) → Choose Mode (Preview/Draft/Send) →
Confirm → Send → Results → Audit Log
```

